My observations

  • Linked data research appears to be segregated from user-centered design trend in libraries. Literature is filled with repetitive, what is linked data? what is a triple? articles
  • linked data for licensed eresource management: nothing at all
  • linked data for commodity book discovery in libraries: nothing significant except hand waving from Zepheira and others
  • linked data for special collections: this is where linked data appears to be getting the most traction in libraries
